ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project

Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.

ElementDescription: Does your spouse or partner ever have four or more drinks in a row? ("In a row" means within 2 hours.)

Notes: 1 = Less than once a month; 2 = 1-2 times a month; 3 = 3-5 times a month; 4 = 6-9 times a month; 5 = 10-15 times a month; 6 = Daily or almost daily
